etymologies: mid 18th century: from French cellulaire, from modern Latin cellularis, from cellula ‘little chamber’, diminutive of cella

definitions: relating to or consisting of living cells
shortDefinitions: relating to or consisting of living cells

definitions: denoting or relating to a mobile telephone system that uses a number of short-range radio stations to cover the area that it serves, the signal being automatically switched from one station to another as the user travels around.
shortDefinitions: denoting or relating to mobile telephone system that uses several short-range radio stations to cover area that it serves

definitions: (of a fabric item, such as a blanket or vest) knitted so as to form holes or hollows that trap air and provide extra insulation.
shortDefinitions: of fabric item knitted so as to form holes or hollows that trap air and provide extra insulation

definitions: consisting of small compartments or rooms
shortDefinitions: consisting of small compartments or rooms
